The output array `perm` is not null.
The length of the output array `perm` is equal to `n`.
The elements in the output array `perm` are positive integers.
The output array `perm` is a permutation of the first `n` positive integers.
The output array `perm` satisfies the condition `encoded[i] = perm[i] XOR perm[i + 1]` for all valid indices `i` in the range [0, `n - 2`].
